Europe
---
Italy (Anzio, Lazio region). 8 Sep 2017. (conf.) 3 cases, apparently locally acquired.
http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-41198774

[Maps of Italy can be accessed at http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/europe/italy_admin_06.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5310090,63107.

This is not the 1st time that there has been local transmission of chikungunya virus in Italy. There was a locally transmitted chikungunya outbreak in 2007 in Emilia Romagna, central Italy. That outbreak was initiated by a viremic individual traveling from India (see Chikungunya - Italy (Emilia Romagna) (04) 20070907.2957)

France (Provence-Alpes-Cote d'Azur). 25 Aug 2017. WHO; as of 23 Aug 2017, (susp.) 8 cases, (probable) 1 case, (conf.) 4 cases.
http://www.who.int/csr/don/25-august-2017-chikungunya-france/en/

[The case count has increased from 2 in the previous August 2017 report to the number given above. The mosquito vector is not stated, but is likely to be _Aedes albopictus_.

Maps of France can be accessed at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France#Administrative_divisions and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5310090,34151. - Mod.TY]

Asia
---
India (national). 4 Aug 2017. (reported) over 12 255 cases. States most affected: Karnataka 8941 cases, Maharashtra 839, Andhra Pradesh 492.
http://theindiasaga.com/saga-corner/national-capital-reeling-under-chikungunya-and-dengue-outbreaks

[A 24-year-old woman from Delhi was reported to have been hospitalized presenting with dark purple-reddish rashes in multiple body parts, very low platelet count, and abnormal kidney function, among others. Her physicians indicated that this is the 1st case report of chikungunya fever presenting severe life-threatening clots in small blood vessels that they have seen (http://tinyurl.com/y7bdd85m).

Maps of India can be accessed at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5310090,142. - Mod.TY]

